# Schema Standards

## Location
All schemas in src/schemas/.
One file per agent output + common.py for shared models.

## Rules
- All fields must have explicit types. No Any.
- All numeric scores: int, ge=0, le=10.
  Document range in field description AND in api-contract.md.
- All list fields: default_factory=list. Never None.
- All enum fields: use Python Enum or Literal types.
- Add Field(description="...") to every field.
  Include unit, range, and example in the description.

## Example
```python
class JobAnalysis(BaseModel):
    scope_clarity_score: int = Field(
        ge=0, le=10,
        description="Clarity of job scope. int 0-10. 10=crystal clear."
    )
    required_skills: list[str] = Field(
        default_factory=list,
        description="Extracted required skills. Empty list if none stated."
    )
```

## No aliases in output schemas
Do not use alias= on fields that appear in agent output.
Aliases cause LLM confusion when field names differ from
JSON keys. Use model_config serialization_alias only where
needed for final API response formatting.
